<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued March 23 at 3:02AM CDT until March 23 at 3:30AM CDT by NWS Mobile</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 330 AM CDT
FOR WESTERN COVINGTON COUNTY...
At 301 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 12 miles southwest
of Andalusia, moving northeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Andalusia, River Falls, Red Level and Heath.
TORNADO...POSSIBLE
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 600 AM CDT for south central
Alabama.
For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
